The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Americans beaten up

 R. KRISHNA DAS

 Raipur, Feb. 2: Two Americans were dragged out of a meeting and beaten up by a group of hooligans who accused them of being involved in religious conversions. 

 Police sources said a meeting was under way at Singh Palace in the Lodhipara area of the Chhattisgarh capital when more than 15 youths armed with sticks and rods arrived there. Harish Patel, who runs an NGO working for the uplift of the poor and organiser of the event, said four American citizens were present at the meeting. 

 The mob entered the hall around 4 pm and dragged out the foreigners. Of the four, two managed to escape. Sources said the rampaging youths beat them up and robbed them. 

 After ransacking the hall, the youths who were shouting anti-conversion slogans fled. The victims filed a police complaint. Senior superintendent of police B.S. Maravi confirmed the incident. 

 K.B. Khatri, a police officer, said the victims were identified as Adam Culley and Jack of New York. The victims left for Delhi by an evening flight. A laptop, a camera and Rs 5,000 in cash were stolen.




